      "rationale": "Power-law exponents alpha and beta and viscosity coefficients were calibrated using the erythrocyte fragility dataset dated 2025-10-01, which predates the February 2026 model revision. The revised turbulence dissipation coupling alters the effective shear stress field seen by the hemolysis sub-model, meaning the pre-revision calibration constants may no longer be consistent with the updated model. Re-calibration against post-revision experimental data is described as planned for Q2 2026 but has not been completed. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation uses the stale parameter distributions, potentially underestimating hemolysis prediction uncertainty."
