    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the simulation evidence package on the basis that achieved credibility factor levels, while below required levels in several factors, were deemed sufficient given the conservative hemolysis safety margin demonstrated at the three validated operating points. The team noted that the erythrocyte fragility calibration dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-01) predates the February 2026 model revision and that re-calibration is planned; this gap was acknowledged but judged acceptable pending Q2 2026 re-validation. The decision reflects residual epistemic uncertainty in model inputs and model form that was not fully resolved at the time of submission.",
